   "s": "err",
   "x": "# Task: Sliding Window Rate Limiter"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "Implement class `SlidingWindowLimiter` in `impl.mjs` (the only file you may edit)."
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "## Spec"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "- `new SlidingWindowLimiter(limit, windowMs)` - allow at most `limit` requests in any sliding window of `windowMs` milliseconds."
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "- `allow(timestampMs)` -> `true` if the request at that timestamp is admitted, `false` if rejected."
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "- Rejected requests do NOT count toward the window."
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "- Timestamps are non-decreasing. The window is inclusive of `now - windowMs + 1` through `now` (i.e. a request at t=0 with windowMs=1000 expires at t=1000)."
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "- Independent instances must not share state."
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "## Examples"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "```js"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "const l = new SlidingWindowLimiter(2, 1000);"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "l.allow(0);    // true"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "l.allow(100);  // true"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "l.allow(500);  // false (2 already in window)"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "l.allow(1000); // true  (t=0 expired)"
  },
  {
   "t": 14014,
   "s": "err",
   "x": "```"
  },
  {
